eadership in the development and supervision of programs, including changes in curriculum, degree programs, and organization, in conjunction with the deans and representatives of the faculty. He provides leadership in the implementation of effective planning in academic affairs, ensures leadership and excellence in academic degree programs and support units. Dr. Graves represents the academic interests of the university in off-campus activities as designated by the President and acts for the President in his absence. Areas of Responsibility: Academic Resources College and Schools Faculty Success Honors International Affairs Library Research, Scholarship & Creative Activities Texas Academy of Mathematics and Science Space Management & Planning UNT Career Connect (QEP) Finley.Graves@unt.edu 940-565-3952 Office Location: Hurley Administration Building, Suite 201 Visit Us   Office of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs370 Hurley Administration Building Mail Us   University of North TexasOffice of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs 1155 Union Circle #311190 Denton, Texas 76203-5017 [map]   Contact Us   940-565-2550 TTY: 940-369-8652 FAX: 940-565-2774 For questions about this website, contact ronda.bewley@unt.edu   Site last updated on: May 09, 2017 Disclaimer  |  AA/EOE/ADA  |  Privacy  |   Electronic Accessibility  |  State of Texas Online  |  Emergency Preparedness  |  THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information  |  UNT Compliance Hotline  |  Governors Committee on People with Disabilities  |  Texas Veterans Portal  |  UNT Home 